The paper deals with scheduling maintenance jobs in networks, which is a problem that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. The focus on maintaining connectivity between two nodes over time suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of algorithms and complexity analysis suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), algorithms (cs.AL), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the mention of preemption and non-preemption suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
